      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "A good race. MARINES CRY (3) has switched yards since a near miss over 1500m at Ascot. Gets in well in easier with the handy 3kg claim and can make an immediate impact for the new camp. BILL SELECTS (4) recorded another minor placing finishing 1.75 lengths away over 1200m at Ascot. Was good there prior and has the class to threaten. IMAPAGETHREE GIRL (1) was safely held last time in a tougher race at Ascot but brought good form to that in more suitable grade. Gets in well with the 3kg claim and is capable of using the inside barrier. Looks well placed here and is a likely improver. HELLO VENETA (7) registered her first win last start over 1300m at Mt Barker, getting home by 1.5 lengths. Sparingly raced and has more to offer. Natasha Faithfull sticks aboard and she cannot be underestimated.",
